2025-08-22 11:16:06,636 - INFO -     [特征生成] ["'new_feature': 'lifestyle_risk_score'  \n'detailed description': This feature calculates a composite lifestyle risk score by normalizing age, scaling the average cigarettes per day by a factor of 1.5, adding 2 for current smokers, subtracting 3 for those not on blood pressure medication, multiplying prevalent hyp by 2, adding the log of glucose (added as a risk factor), and then summing all these elements. The final score is divided by the mean of bmi to adjust for body mass differences.  \n'brief description': A lifestyle risk score combining smoking habits, hypertension, medication, and metabolic factors.  \n'relevant': ['age', 'currentsmoker', 'cigsperday', 'bpmeds', 'prevalenthyp', 'bmi', 'glucose']", "'new_feature': 'chd_risk_index'\n\n'detailed description': This feature is computed by first calculating the standard normalized value of glucose level for patients who are not current smokers and have no prevalent stroke. Next, the mean of the systolic blood pressure (sysbp) is multiplied by 0.8 for female patients who are on blood pressure medication. Then, find the logarithm of the sum of totchol and half of the bmi for patients with diabetes. These components are combined with weights of 1, 0.8, and 0.5 respectively. The final result is derived by dividing this weighted sum by the age of the patient, effectively capturing an adjusted coronary heart disease risk index.\n\n'brief description': A composite heart disease risk index based on glucose, blood pressure, cholesterol, and age.\n\n'relevant': ['glucose', 'currentsmoker', 'prevalentstroke', 'sysbp', 'gender', 'bpmeds', 'totchol', 'bmi', 'diabetes', 'age']", "'new_feature': 'health_risk_indicator'  \n'detailed description': This feature is calculated by combining several health indicators. It is computed as the sum of the normalized glucose level, normalized body mass index (BMI), and the normalized systolic blood pressure (sysbp). Each of these components is standardized by subtracting the mean and dividing by the standard deviation within the dataset. The health_risk_indicator provides an overall measure of a patient's health risk factors, assuming equal weight to glucose, BMI, and systolic blood pressure.  \n'brief description': A composite indicator combining normalized glucose, BMI, and systolic blood pressure.  \n'relevant': ['glucose', 'bmi', 'sysbp']"]
